                "CONTROLLER TECHNICAL (PORT REX POWER STATION) GENERATION DIVISION\nVacancy type: External/Internal\nTask Grade : T10\nArea of Specialization : To control the operations of the generation unit and to maintain the mechanical plant\nDepartment : Maintenance \uff06 Operations\nBusiness Unit : Peaking Operating Unit\nLocation : South Africa (Eastern Cape)\nReference Number : 49371059 CV/Gx Peak\nClosing Date : 11/13/2023\n \nMinimum Requirements\nQualification(s):\nGrade 12/NCV4/NSC3 with Maths and Science at NQF4 with 120 credits plus Trade Test\nor\nNational Certificate in Gas Power Plant Auxiliary Systems Operations at NQF4 with 120 credits applicable to gas stations or National Certificate in Hydro Power Plant Auxiliary Systems Operations NQF4 with 120 credits applicable to hydro stations\n\nRelated Experience:\n\u2022 2 years\u2019 related technical experience in maintenance environment\n \nSkills and Competencies\nBehavioural:\no Honesty\no Integrity\no Professionalism\n\n\u2022 Leadership:\no Team player\no Motivating teams\no Coaching and mentoring\n\n\u2022 Knowledge:\no Root cause analyses\no Electrical desk operations\no Quality control\no Project management\no Basic operating\no High voltage (HV) low voltage (LV) regulations\no Plant Safety Regulations\n\n\u2022 Skills\no Analytical and problem solving skills\no Communications skills\no Computer literacy skills\no Supervisory skills\n \nKey Responsibilities\n\u2022 Perform operating activities\n\u2022 Take out plant permits.\n\u2022 Perform administrative duties.\n\u2022 Maintain electrical or mechanical plant equipment.\n\u2022 Assist with modifications.\n\u2022 Ensure availability of correct spares and materials.\n\u2022 Perform stand by duties.\n\u2022 Supervise contractors, Eskom employee activities during outages.\n\n\n FOR ASSISTANCE WITH THIS ADVERT, PLEASE EMAIL\nrecuitmentgx@eskom.co.za\n \nKindly apply for the position online by clicking on the link below:\n\u201cIf you have not been contacted within 28 days after the closing date of this advertisement, please accept that your application was unsuccessful.\u201d\n \n\u201cEskom is committed to equality, employment equity, and diversity. In accordance with the employment equity plan of Eskom and its employment equity goals and targets, preference may be given, but is not limited, to candidates from under-represented designated groups.  Eskom reserves the right not to make an appointment to the posts as advertised.\nCandidates with disabilities are encouraged to apply for positions.\u201d\nEskom is committed to providing a smoke-free environment for its employees and visitors at the workplace.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE"
